    "subs": [
        {
            "text": "WordLand v0.50",
            "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 21:55:35 GMT",
            "type": "outline",
            "subs": [
                {
                    "text": "<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vxdv5PveIDM\">Adding and deleting categories</a> are part of \"WordLand\" 0.50, released earlier today. These are the same categories you can edit in the WordPress user interface. But I learned that you need to be able to add categories when you're writing. You want this functionality to be close-by. ",
                    "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 16:15:48 GMT",
                    "type": "outline",
                    "flInCalendar": true
                },
                {
                    "text": "<a href=\"https://imgs.scripting.com/2025/03/16/twoColumnScreenShot.png\">Two columns</a> in the Categories dialog. More efficient use of space.",
                    "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 21:55:18 GMT",
                    "type": "outline",
                    "flInCalendar": true
                },
                {
                    "text": "<a href=\"https://imgs.scripting.com/2025/03/16/contextMenuScreenShot.png\">Context menu</a> with two new commands.",
                    "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:01:19 GMT",
                    "flInCalendar": true
                },
                {
                    "text": "Change notes <a href=\"https://github.com/scripting/wordlandSupport/issues/59\">are here</a>.",
                    "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:01:56 GMT",
                    "flInCalendar": true
                }
            ],
            "flInCalendar": true
        },
        {
            "text": "Blogging is due for a refresh",
            "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:20:22 GMT",
            "type": "outline",
            "subs": [
                {
                    "text": "A lot has changed since the last time we took a serious look at blogging. A few items, as examples.",
                    "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:20:28 GMT",
                    "flNumberedSubs": "true",
                    "subs": [
                        {
                            "text": "When RSS came along Markdown didn't exist. The two technologies belong together, imho.",
                            "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:20:34 GMT",
                            "flInCalendar": true
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Websockets have replaced long polling. ",
                            "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:20:51 GMT",
                            "flInCalendar": true
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Servers got cheap! (and easy to deploy).",
                            "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:20:53 GMT",
                            "flInCalendar": true
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "SQL is fast and the tools are much better.",
                            "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:20:54 GMT",
                            "flInCalendar": true
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "The user interfaces of all the Web 2.0+ products didn't exist last time we created new blogging communities. We can borrow ideas from  twitter-like systems, even huge products like Facebook and Spotify have innovations that come long after the initial wave of blogging.",
                            "created": "Sun, 16 Mar 2025 22:20:35 GMT",
                            "flInCalendar": true
                        }
                    ],
                    "flInCalendar": true
                },
                {
                    "text": "But one thing stays the same -- all the components are replaceable. Absolutely zero lock-in. We use simple standard APIs where they exist, and create new minimal formats and protocols where they don't.",
                    "flInCalendar": true
                },
                {
                    "text": "Blogging has a simple philosophy that remains constant. ",
                    "flInCalendar": true
                }
            ],
            "flInCalendar": true
        }
    ]
}